title: Open small businesses change
caption: Comparison between 2019 (baseline) and subsequent years' daily number of open small businesses within 1 February, 2020 and 21 June, 2021 in Austin, TX.
insights: Between mid-March and mid-April, 2020 there was a mean decline of -28% in the number of small open small businesses across all sectors compared to 2019.
The leisure and hospitality sector has had the lowest decline of -84%.

The spike towards the baseline in the beginning of July, 2020 could be attributed to 4th of July celebration where already low numbers of small busniesses open which in comparison to the pandemic period, is similar.
